name: Customer
desc: Represents a customer with personal information.

name: Customer
desc: Creates a new instance of the Customer class.

name: ID
desc:
A static counter to generate unique IDs for customers.
This ensures that each new customer gets a unique identifier.

name: address
desc: The address of the customer.

name: birthday
desc: The birthdate of the customer.

name: firstname
desc: The first name of the customer.

name: id
desc: The unique identifier for the customer. This field is the primary key.

name: lastname
desc: The last name of the customer.

name: CustomerDAO
desc: A Data Access Object (DAO) for managing CRUD operations for Customer entities.

name: deleteCustomer
desc:
Deletes a Customer from the database。
Takes a Customer object as a parameter.
Returns the number of rows affected.

name: findCustomer
desc:
Finds a customer by its id.
Returns a single Customer object if found, otherwise null.

name: getAllCustomers
desc:
Retrieves all customers from the database.
Returns a list of Customer objects.

name: insertCustomer
desc:
Inserts a new Customer into the database.
Takes a Customer object as a parameter.

name: updateCustomer
desc:
Updates an existing Customer in the database.
Takes a Customer object as a parameter.

name: CustomerListPage
desc:
A page that displays a list of customers and provides functionality
for adding, updating, and deleting customer records.

desc: Creates the database and initializes it.

name: databaseBuilder
desc:
Creates a database builder for a persistent database.
Once a database is built, you should keep a reference to it and re-use it.

name: inMemoryDatabaseBuilder
desc:
Creates a database builder for an in memory database.
Information stored in an in memory database disappears when the process is killed.
Once a database is built, you should keep a reference to it and re-use it.
